Exact Regional Visibility using Line Space Partitioning

Jiří Bittner, Jan Prikryl
Exact Regional Visibility using Line Space Partitioning
TR-186-2-01-06, March 2001 [paper]

Information

  • Publication Type: Technical Report
  • Workgroup(s)/Project(s): not specified
  • Date: March 2001
  • Number: TR-186-2-01-06
  • Keywords: projective geometry, Plücker coordinates, kD--tree, BSP--tree, line--space, visibility

Abstract

We present a new technique for exact and output sensitive determination of visibility from a polygonal region in the plane. It uses hierarchical partitioning of line space, that provides comprehensive description of visibility for a set of occluders. To the best of our knowledge, it is the first exact regional visibility algorithm suitable for visibility preprocessing of large scenes of unspecific type. We have evaluated the implementation on scenes with various visibility characteristics.
